<br>
Seeing that the Hydra was an immortal creature. She stocked up on the special arrows that her father bestowed only to her. The only weapon, besides his lightning bolts that could destroy another immortal. <br>
<br>
She knew that the hydra was partial to the Aegean Sea, thats why she thought it weird that it would of found its way all the way to Themiscrya without having a reason. Something told her inside, there was something more to this story, and dang it, Artemis would find out exactly what it was.<br>
<br>
She would start at the scene of the deed, and make her way to the Agean if the Hydra was not found by then. She knew what Islands the Hydra's inhabited, and knew exactly which one she would take care of, and thats all she needed to know.<br>
<br>
Vanishing from her chambers upon Olympus, she appeared aside the river that Erin was swimming in when she was attacked and looked for the evidence that would not be seen by the human or anyone elses, besides the Olympians eye. <p>~ The Silver Goddess~&lt;br&gt;<br>
