<br>
Heading further downstream, she came to the end of the the river, then frowned. No other evidence. Guessing evidence was useless anyway, seeing as she knew the culprit, she figured she would have to head to the Island herself.<br>
<br>
&quot;I do not know your exact position Thanatos, but if you can hear me, meet me on the Island of Melos, that is the home to many Hydra's, this one as well.&quot;<br>
<br>
She said outloud. If the hydra was not at the island, she knew, it would come back sooner or later, it was its home, and Artemis had tons of patience when it came to bringing to justice anyone, or anything, that harmed the amazons.<br>
<br>
She began to fdade out, then in a silvery burst, she appeared on Melos. Bows and Arrows ready, thought, she did not think a hydra was stupid enough to harm an Olympian, let alone the daughter of Zeus himself. But if the hydra was being controlled by someone, she was not willing to take the risk, nor was she against shooting first. <p>~ The Silver Goddess~<br><br>
